# Data model

## IDs

- `document`, `category`, `tag`: `uuid().primaryKey().defaultRandom()`
- `site_settings`: singleton row `id = 'default'`

## Tables

- `category` — fixed seed: getting-started, guides, reference, examples, changelog
- `document` — slug unique, title, content (markdown), excerpt, published, categoryId
- `tag` + `document_tag` — many-to-many tags on documents
- `site_settings` — site branding, landing hero, defaults

## Migrations

- Use `pnpm run db:generate` then `pnpm run db:push --force` for schema changes
- Seed categories and default settings in `src/lib/server/db/seed.ts`

## Slugs

- Auto-generate from title (kebab-case) when slug empty on save
- Admin can override slug manually
